  "prompt": "If I connect USB OTG pendrive to my power bank and connect the other point with data cable to my mobile, will pendrive be working on my mobile?",
  "response": "When you connect a USB OTG (On-The-Go) pendrive to a power bank and then use a data cable to connect the power bank to your mobile phone, the setup you've described is unlikely to work as intended for accessing the pendrive's data on your mobile. Here's why:\n\n1. **USB OTG Functionality**: USB OTG allows a device, such as a smartphone, to act as a host and connect to USB devices like a pendrive. However, the power bank in your setup does not typically support OTG functionality; it's designed primarily to supply power.\n\n2. **Power Bank Role**: A power bank usually only provides power and does not facilitate data transfer between connected devices. When you connect your mobile to the power bank, it will charge your phone but won't enable data communication between your phone and the pendrive.\n\n3. **Direct Connection Required**: For the pendrive to work with your mobile, you need a direct OTG connection. This means using an OTG cable or adapter that connects the pendrive directly to your phone. Your phone must also support OTG functionality.\n\nTo successfully access the pendrive on your mobile:\n\n- Use an OTG cable or adapter.\n- Connect the pendrive directly to your phone using the OTG cable.\n- Ensure your phone supports USB OTG.\n\nIf you follow these steps, you should be able to access the data on the pendrive through your mobile device.",
